Initial EDA Plots

How many kids produce each kind of sound?

sounds %>% 
  group_by(sound) %>% 
  summarize(total_produce = sum(kids_produce)) %>% 
  knitr::kable()
sound total_produce
cockadoodledoo 148
meow 681
woof woof 940 
ggplot(sounds, aes(x = sound, y = kids_produce)) + 
  geom_col() +
  labs(x = "Sound", y = "Total Children Producing")

Challenge #2: Mapping at the Geom Level

ggplot(sounds, aes(x = age, y = prop_produce)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color = sound), size = 2) +

Challenge #3: geom_line()

ggplot(sounds, aes(x = age, y = prop_produce)) + 
  geom_line(aes(group = sound)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = sound), size = 2) +
  labs(x = "Age (months)", y = "Proportion of Children Producing")

Challenge #4: Combining Points and Lines

ggplot(sounds, aes(x = age, y = prop_produce, color = sound)) + 
  geom_line() +
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  labs(x = "Age (months)", y = "Proportion of Children Producing") 

ggplot(sounds, aes(x = age, y = prop_produce, color = sound)) + 
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE, lwd = .5) +
  geom_point(size = 2)  +
  labs(x = "Age (months)", y = "Proportion of Children Producing") 
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'

sounds <- sounds %>% 
  mutate(sound = as.factor(sound))

sound_traj <- ggplot(sounds, aes(x = age, 
                         y = prop_produce, 
                         color = fct_reorder2(sound, age, prop_produce))) +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE, lwd = .5) +
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  labs(x = "Age (months)", 
       y = "Proportion of Children Producing", 
       color = "sound")
sound_traj
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'

Challenge #5: Fill and Color Aesthetics

ggplot(sounds, aes(x = age, 
                   y = prop_produce, 
                   fill = fct_reorder2(sound, age, prop_produce))) + 
  geom_smooth(aes(color = fct_reorder2(sound, age, prop_produce)),
              se = FALSE, lwd = .5, show.legend = FALSE) +
  geom_point(size = 2, shape = 21) +
  labs(x = "Age (months)", 
       y = "Proportion of Children Producing", 
       fill = "sound")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'

Challenge #6: Combining Aesthetic Encodings

ggplot(sounds, aes(x = age, 
                   y = prop_produce, 
                   fill = fct_reorder2(sound, age, prop_produce))) + 
  geom_smooth(aes(color = fct_reorder2(sound, age, prop_produce)),
              se = FALSE, lwd = .5, show.legend = FALSE) +
  geom_point(size = 2, shape = 21) +
  labs(x = "Age (months)", 
       y = "Proportion of Children Producing", 
       fill = "sound") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("cornflowerblue", 
                               "seagreen", "coral")) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("cornflowerblue", 
                               "seagreen", "coral"))

                   y = prop_produce,

Part 1: Good and careful color!

storm_plot <- ggplot(storm1995, aes(x = Latitude, 
                         y = Longitude, 
                         color = fct_reorder2(Name, Latitude, Longitude))) +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE, lwd = .5) +
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  labs(x = "Latitude", 
       y = "Longitude", 
       color = "Name")
storm_plot +  scale_color_manual(values = beyonce_palette(18)[c(1, 4, 5)])
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'

The plot displays the trajectories of three hurricanes that occurred in 1995. Each point represents a recorded location of the hurricane, with the color indicating the name of the hurricane. The chosen color palette prioritizes contrast and visibility for people with color blindness.

Part 2: Greyscale!

ggplot(storm1995, aes(x = Latitude, y = Longitude, 
                   fill = fct_reorder2(Name, Latitude, Longitude))) + 
  geom_smooth(aes(color = fct_reorder2(Name, Latitude, Longitude),
                  lty = fct_reorder2(Name, Latitude, Longitude)),
              se = FALSE, lwd = .5, show.legend = FALSE) +
  geom_point(size = 2, shape = 21) +
  labs(x = "Latitude", 
       y = "Longitude", 
       fill = "Name") +
  scale_fill_grey(start = 0.2, end = 0.8) +
  scale_color_grey(start = 0.2, end = 0.8)

ggplot(storm1995, aes(x = Wind, y = Pressure)) +

This plot failed to visualize data. It is hard to see the relationship between wind and pressure in different hurricane.
